This folder contains useful tools for developers.

analyze-git-diff.rb
  This script is used to analyze the git-diff result.

clear-trailing-whitespace.rb
  Clear all trailing white space in a file.
  Usage: ./clear-whiltespace.rb <path-to-file>

git-remove-history.sh
  Removes some files permanently from git history.
  Useful when you made mistakes by adding useless files.
  You must run this script in nova's root code directory (where .git is located).
  Usage: ./git-remove-history.sh <path-to-file>

install-git-centos.sh
  Install git from source on CentOS.
  Requires Internet connection.

make_tar.py
  Create a distribution package. The package will be put at nova's root code directory.
  Usage:  "./make_tar.py" will create a package from current git HEAD.
          "./make_tar.py <tag-name>" will create a package from a certain git tag.

nova.vimrc
  This file provides some useful settings for vim.

replace-tab-to-space.rb
  Replace the leading tabs to spaces.
  Usage: ./replace-tab-to-space.rb <path-to-file>

rsync_centos_repo.sh
  It will create a mirror of CentOS repositories.

style-check.rb
  Check coding style of all source code files in Nova.
  You can fix all the bad styles with an '-f' option.
  Usage: ./style-check.rb

